   especially oribatid mites as well as on their species diversity.
   Tectocepheus velatus was the most abundant species among the oribatid
   mites on all the stands of littleleaf linden cultivation. Abundance
   dynamics of this oribatid species in the two-years period of the study,
   especially on the variant with mulching and organic fertilization,
